Cinema => When in Chennai, do not miss a chance to watch a movie. Chennai is the best place to watch a movie. Make sure to book your tickets in advance especially in the weekend, because most of the cinemas will be sold out. Chennai also provides best cinematic experience at lowest cost Rs. 120/- and lesser, which is very less compared to other metro cities like Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, Hyderabad and Kolkata. There are several cinemas in the city. Check out any local newspaper or websites to get to know the movies running in and around Chennai. Visit [21] to get the details of movies currently running in Chennai. Some of the cinema halls are

Udhayam Theatre, Ashok Pillar, Chennai
Devi Cineplex , [22].  In the heart of Chennai on Anna Salai. The Cineplex is a huge complex and a great architectural beauty.

Sathyam Cine Complex [23], Thiru-vi-ka Rd, phone 044-42244224. One of the best theaters. Provides quality food and the main screen is one of the biggest in INDIA.
Escape Cinemas [24], Express Avenue, Royapettah, phone 044-4224 4224
Inox [25], Chennai Citi Centre, R.K.Salai
Mayajaal Cine Complex [26], ECR. 14 Screen Multiplex.
Abhirami Cine Complex, Purasawalkam. 
Shanti Cine Complex, Anna Salai
Ega theatres [27], p.h road, Kilpauk (Features Hindi movies).
Sangam cine complex in kilpauk. For tickets check www.ticketnew.com.
Rohini Cinema Complex, Koyambedu.
Ganga Theatre complex in Kolathur.
Rakki Theatre in Ambattur.
PVR, AMPA SkyWalk Mall,Nelson Manickam Road.
AGS Royal,Villivakkam.
AGS Cinemas OMR,Navalur.
 Vetri Theatre, Chromepet.


